This sequence consistently boosts the value of small and medium-sized creatures significantly. However, **do NOT use this sequence on large creatures** (e.g., elephants, pandas, whales, sharks, giraffes) as it will drastically reduce their value, often to zero or negative. Once you have 2-3 high-value small/medium creatures after applying the MGMG sequence, combine them. Combining three creatures from different environments (e.g., land, water, air) that have gone through the full MGMG process yields the highest scores (typically 85-95).

message: Hello future player! Here are some tips: Always process creatures using the pattern: Mutation Catalyst > Growth Serum > Mutation Catalyst. For small and medium creatures, a final Growth Serum will maximize their individual value (small: 25, medium: 30). However, for large creatures, applying the final Growth Serum usually drops their value to 0; stop at 'grown super-mutant' (value 30). After processing, combine up to three creatures for high scores (60-95). Combining creatures with diverse features (e.g., land, water, air, different sizes) seems to yield better results. Do NOT apply tools to items that are already 'super-grown super-mutant' or to complex hybrids, as this will likely corrupt them and lose value. Submit when you have a valuable 3-creature hybrid. Good luck!

message: To maximize your score, always follow this enhancement sequence for three different creatures: Mutation Catalyst > Growth Serum > Mutation Catalyst > Growth Serum. Apply it to one 'lives on land' creature, one 'lives in the water' creature, and one 'lives in the air' creature.
